<title>FRANCE: L'Oreal Q1 sales rise 11.2 pct.</title>
<headline>L'Oreal Q1 sales rise 11.2 pct.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-04-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>Three months to March 31, 1996</p>
<p>(All figures in billions of French francs)</p>
<p>    Turnover					16.5	up 11.2 pct</p>
<p>NOTE - L'Oreal said in a statement that first-quarter 1997 consolidated sales rose 11.2 percent, or 6.3 percent on a comparable basis.</p>
<p>Changes in structure -- the consolidations of Maybelline since February 12, 1996, of Giuliani SA since October 1, 1996, and Henning Berlin GmbH since November 1 -- had a positive impact of 1.6 percent. Exchange rate movements, particularly the U.S. dollar rise, had a positive impact of 3.3 percent, it said.</p>
<p>-- Paris Newsroom +33 1 4221 5452</p>
